ENTRY       EC 1.13.11.66               Enzyme
NAME        hydroquinone 1,2-dioxygenase;
            hydroquinone dioxygenase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen (oxygenases);
            With incorporation of two atoms of oxygen
SYSNAME     benzene-1,4-diol:oxygen 1,2-oxidoreductase (decyclizing)
REACTION    benzene-1,4-diol + O2 = (2E,4Z)-4-hydroxy-6-oxohexa-2,4-dienoate [RN:R05246]
ALL_REAC    R05246
SUBSTRATE   benzene-1,4-diol [CPD:C00530];
            O2 [CPD:C00007]
PRODUCT     (2E,4Z)-4-hydroxy-6-oxohexa-2,4-dienoate
COMMENT     The enzyme is an extradiol-type dioxygenase, and is a member of the nonheme-iron(II)-dependent dioxygenase family. It catalyses the ring cleavage of a wide range of hydroquinone substrates to produce the corresponding 4-hydroxymuconic semialdehydes.
